I.—1225, November 17. Agreement made between the Lord King's Burgesses of Nottingham and the men of the Borough of Retdford, whereby the Burgesses of Nottingham let to the Burgesses of Retdford their toll. Made on the same day, to the same effect, and with the same witnesses as the grant printed at p. 18 (No. X.)

4218.
